{# ── DEFINITION · real H2 carrying the specialty-trades definition prose. (H2: Specialty trade contractor accounting, plainly.) ── #}
<section class="section" id="trade-definition">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">In plain terms</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Specialty trade contractor accounting, plainly.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      {%- for p in definition %}<p>{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── AI SUMMARY · five-question block. NON-heading questions (baseline <dt>). (H2: Specialty trade accounting, in five questions.) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="trade-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Specialty trade accounting, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <p class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</p>
        <div class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── CHALLENGES · three places trade contractors lose the numbers (grid-3 buyer-cards). (H2 + 3 H3s) ── #}
<section class="section" id="trade-challenges">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Why trade-contractor books break</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Three places service-and-replacement trades lose the numbers.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Almost every messy HVAC, plumbing, or electrical file fails in the same three areas. Knowing which one you&rsquo;re in tells us where to start.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for c in challenges %}
      <div class="buyer-card">
        <p class="buyer-card__opener">{{ c.signal | safe }}</p>
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">{{ c.title | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ c.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── SUB-VERTICALS · the specialty trades we serve (grid-3 stack-8). (H2 + 6 H3s) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="trade-trades">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Who we serve</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">One engagement model across the service trades.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Each specialty trade has its own parts intensity, install-versus-service mix, and ticket profile &mdash; but the accounting backbone is shared: cost the ticket, defer the agreement, reconcile the financing, tie out the FSM platform. The engagement model &mdash; fixed-fee, written scope, named ProAdvisor, work in your own QuickBooks file &mdash; stays consistent.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for t in trades %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <h3>{{ t.title | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ t.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── WHAT WE HANDLE · the six services (grid-3 stack-8). (H2 + 6 H3s) ── #}
<section class="section" id="trade-handle">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What TechBrot handles</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Trade-contractor accounting, done by an expert.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Every engagement is scoped to your trade, tech and truck count, agreement volume, financing volume, FSM platform, and any prevailing-wage work, delivered in your own QuickBooks file by a named Certified ProAdvisor.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for s in handle %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <h3><a href="{{ s.href }}">{{ s.title | safe }}</a></h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── INTEGRATIONS · trade tools reconciled with QuickBooks (checks-list). (H2: Connected to your trade-service stack.) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="trade-integrations">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Tools we work alongside</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Connected to your trade-service stack.</h2>
    </header>
    <ul class="checks-list">
      {%- for t in integrations %}<li>{{ t | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
    </ul>
    <p class="prose">{{ integrationsNote | safe }}</p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── COMPARISON TABLE · vs-scroll + vs-table (no collapse, T3). Per-ticket costing vs month-total bookkeeping. ── #}
<section class="section" id="trade-comparison">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Why generic books miss trade economics</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Per-ticket trade costing vs. month-total bookkeeping.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">The structural differences that explain why a standard P&amp;L can show a profitable month while individual service calls and trucks quietly lose money &mdash; and why trade contractors need the books built at the ticket level.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="vs-scroll">
      <table class="vs-table">
        <caption class="sr-only">Per-ticket specialty-trade costing versus month-total generic bookkeeping compared</caption>
        <thead><tr><th scope="col">What the books need to handle</th><th scope="col" class="vs-table__us">Per-ticket trade costing (TechBrot)</th><th scope="col">Month-total generic bookkeeping</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          {%- for r in comparison %}
          <tr><th scope="row">{{ r.row | safe }}</th><td class="vs-table__us"><span class="vs-table__concede">{{ r.us | safe }}</span></td><td><span class="vs-table__concede">{{ r.them | safe }}</span></td></tr>
          {%- endfor %}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="prose">{{ comparisonNote | safe }}</p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── PROCESS · four-phase engagement rhythm (process-diagram). (H2 + 4 H3s) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="trade-process">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">How engagements work</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">From mixed-up tickets to margin per call and per truck.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Every trade-contractor engagement follows the same four-phase rhythm &mdash; per-ticket costing, agreement deferral, financing and FSM reconciliation, and tech/truck profitability accurate first, before anyone makes hiring, pricing, or fleet-expansion decisions.</p>
    </header>
    <ol class="process-diagram">
      {%- for s in process %}
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">{{ s.num | safe }}</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">{{ s.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
      </li>
      {%- endfor %}
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── ADVISORY · standing brand line carried as section prose (no gutting). (H2: Margin per ticket is the start. The right next truck is the point.) ── #}
<section class="section" id="trade-advisory">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Beyond the books</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Margin per ticket is the start. The right next hire is the point.</h2>
    </header>
